# Deployment and Service Management

## Service Setup
- Use [taskun.service](mdc:taskun.service) for systemd integration
- Run [setup_autostart.sh](mdc:setup_autostart.sh) to install and enable service
- Service runs as root to access hardware devices
- Auto-starts on boot for standalone operation

## Manual Operation
- Use [start_taskun_manually.sh](mdc:start_taskun_manually.sh) for manual startup
- Use [stop_taskun_service.sh](mdc:stop_taskun_service.sh) to stop service
- SSH access available for remote control
- Keyboard controls (W/S/Enter) work without OLED/joystick

## Dependencies
- Install packages from [requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt)
- Enable I2C interface in raspi-config
- Ensure proper permissions for device access
- Install TASBot firmware on CY8CKIT-059

## Hardware Setup
- Connect OLED display to I2C pins (SDA: GPIO2, SCL: GPIO3)
- Connect USB gamepad for navigation
- Connect CY8CKIT-059 via USB for TASBot communication
- Connect NES console and controller adapter

## Troubleshooting
- Check I2C device detection with `i2cdetect -y 1`
- Verify joystick device at `/dev/input/js0`
- Monitor service logs with `journalctl -u taskun.service`
- Use stop file `/tmp/taskun_stop` for external shutdown
